		<h1 class="aboutHeader">Mission Statement:</h1>
		<hr class="divider">
		<h2 class="aboutHeaderComment">Gegatron exists to create community that encourages quality storytelling and creativity in the science fiction and fantasy genres.</h2>
		<hr class="divider">
		<p>We love stories. That is the basis of who we are. It 		doesn’t matter if they come in the form of books, movies, art, dance, 			theatre, song or some other genre I have left out, we love them all. We 		love the way that a good story can take you out of this world and place you 	some where completely different. We love stories that make us question what 	we believe and how we think. We love stories that lead to hours of 				discussion and bring us closer together as friends. We want to create these 	types of stories.<br>
			<br>
			And we want to share them with you.<br>
			<br>	
			Currently, Gegatron is run by three individuals that you will come to know as geggiskhan, bingo, and damselyse. We are all big fat geeks. We have noticed recently that though there are some truly incredible things available to us through network T.V. and companies like Marvel or TOR, we are enjoying some of the things we discover on-line even more. There are hundreds of talented people in the world that will never get published just because they don’t know the right people; artwork that will never get shown because someone decided illustrations aren’t what sell well in galleries. We want to help bring these stories to the world.<br>
			<br>
			Gegatron is a place that we can try new things that have never been done; a place that stories can be told without someone tweaking them to help make them “sell” better. We wanted a place where we could share our work with the world even if it isn’t what typically sells, and we want to give other people this opportunity as well someday soon. Right now it is just the three of us and we are messily figuring out how to make everything work, but soon we hope to bring others in and create a community that can encourage each other to be better at the things we love doing.<br>
			<br>
		</p>
